Median income

library(tidyverse)
library(tidycensus)

The table

I had to filter for:

  • the table id in name
  • the column name “Median income (dollars)” in label.

The values we want is: S1903_C01_001

get_acs(
  year = 2019,
  variables = "S1903_C03_001",
  geography = "us"
)
Getting data from the 2015-2019 5-year ACS
Using the ACS Subject Tables

Now that we have confirmed it, let’s fetch it by counties in Texas

tx_median <- get_acs(
  year = 2019,
  variables = "S1903_C03_001",
  geography = "county",
  state = "TX",
)
Getting data from the 2015-2019 5-year ACS
Using the ACS Subject Tables
Using FIPS code '48' for state 'TX'
tx_median

Lowest

tx_median %>% 
  arrange(estimate) %>% 
  head(10)

Highest

tx_median %>% 
  arrange(desc(estimate)) %>% 
  head(10)

Now to plot it

First add geometry to the data

tx_median_geo <- get_acs(
  year = 2019,
  variables = "S1903_C03_001",
  geography = "county",
  state = "TX",
  # add geometry
  geometry = TRUE
)

ggplot(tx_median_geo) + 
  geom_sf(aes(fill = estimate)) +
  theme_void() +
  labs(
    title = "2019 Median Income in Texas counties",
    caption = "Source: Census Bureau/ACS 5-year 2019"
  ) +
  scale_fill_distiller(
    palette = "Greens",
    direction = 1,
    name = "Median income",
    label = dollar
  )
